			<description><![CDATA[<p>
Verimatrix is&nbsp;looking for <strong>Senior QA Engineers</strong>, committed to quality and professional excellence, who desire to lead and participate in the test effort of state-of-the-art Video Content Security products, in a fast-paced environment.</p>
<p>
<strong>ESSENTIAL DUTIES &amp; RESPONSIBILITIES</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Estimate, design, and execute tests and accurately and concisely report both progress and defect status via Test Case and Defect Tracking databases, tracking issues to resolution.&nbsp; Test all product deliverables for professional work, including the product, installation of product, and User Documentation for product.</li>
<li>
Write and execute tests that verify internal API functions, user interface, and interoperability with between product modules.</li>
<li>
Lead assigned QA activities through entire development cycle (Requirements, Design, Test Development/Execution, and Verification &amp; Validation.) Review requirements, design, code, test cases, and other documentation for potential issues. Work with the development team, project management, and network operations to ensure that requirements are verifiable.</li>
<li>
Plan, size, and schedule testing activities accordingly.&nbsp; Develop Test Strategies and Master Test Plans.</li>
<li>
Set up networked (IP) equipment for video content security tests in Windows, Linux, and Solaris.</li>
<li>
Work with Development and Customer Care Departments to better characterize defects.</li>
<li>
Lead improvements to existing quality processes, including processes spanning multiple departments; lead the development of organization-wide quality plans.</li>
<li>
Lead and mentor others in all the above.</li>
<li>
Position may focus on Functional, System, Automation, or Performance Testing.</li>
<li>
Other duties may be assigned as needed by the Department.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>QUALIFICATION REQUIREMENTS</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree in Computer Science, Mathematics, EE or similar field is required. Further professional certifications/professional growth achievements are a plus.</li>
<li>
5-7 years real world testing experience, three of which include leading projects.</li>
<li>
Excellent understanding of typical software engineering practices (Defect Tracking, Test Case Management, Lifecycle models.)&nbsp; Experience with Agile methods is a plus.</li>
<li>
Experience with Backend/Application Server Testing is essential. Tester-level proficiency in LinuxWinSolaris.</li>
<li>
Knowledge of network principles and of TCP/UDP/IP technology required.&nbsp; Previous experience testing internet video products is a plus.</li>
<li>
Understanding of Relational Databases and use of basic SQL commands.</li>
<li>
Excellent analytical skills.&nbsp; Root cause analysis in both software bugs and in processes.</li>
<li>
Experience in QA activities for unit, component, system, smoke, regression, and automated testing.&nbsp; Proven methodic approach to these is required (equivalence tests, boundary tests, state-transition, orthogonal arrays).</li>
<li>
Proven good scripting/coding skills. Understanding of Coding Concepts such as OOP.</li>
<li>
Excellent attention to detail and follow-through.</li>
<li>
Excellent ability to work independently, in team, and in leading a team.</li>
<li>
Personal Traits: Strong written, verbal, and presentation skills.&nbsp; Excellent interpersonal skills.&nbsp; Self-motivated and energetic team player.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Each of the Following would be a Plus:</strong><br />
&bull; Digital Rights Management<br />
&bull; Experience in a security organization<br />
&bull; JDBC<br />
&bull; NoSQL<br />
&bull; OCI<br />
&bull; ODBC<br />
&bull; Oracle certification<br />
&bull; Server and application programming in Linux, OS X, or Windows<br />
&bull; Service-oriented architecture<br />
&bull; Video Conditional Access Systems<br />
&bull; Video standards such as: DECE/UltraViolet, MPEG2/4, AVC, H.264, MPEG DASH, HTTP Live Streaming, PlayReady, Marlin and RTSP<br />
&bull; Virtualization<br />
&bull; Windows Media</p>
