			<description><![CDATA[<p>
A <strong>Senior Integration Test and Certification Engineer</strong> at Verimatrix participates in the integration of our multiple products into set top boxes for use by our clients and partners.&nbsp; Our product suite enables content protection and security for video delivered via satellite, cable, or the Internet.&nbsp; The integration test and certification engineer collaborates with his/her teammates to deliver high-performing, scalable, high-quality products.&nbsp; The engineer should enjoy working through the software development lifecycle.&nbsp; A successful engineer will be proactive, interactive, creative, and flexible.&nbsp; The engineer will need to learn and understand the entire Verimatrix product suite as well as gain deep technical knowledge of set top box integrations.&nbsp; The engineer will work with Verimatrix partners, suppliers, and customers frequently so the engineer needs excellent communication skills and a professional manner.&nbsp; We are a global company and appreciate people with global awareness and knowledge.&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<strong>Some tasks the integration test and certification engineer will have:&nbsp;</strong></p>
<p>
&bull; Communicate with hardware manufacturers about hardware integration tools and documentation<br />
&bull; Assist with security reviews of implementation and hardware configuration<br />
&bull; Support partner companies in applying our SDKs<br />
&bull; Support other teams on product technical issues such as product usage, problem analysis<br />
&bull; Estimate, design, and execute tests and accurately and concisely report both progress and defect status via test case and defect tracking databases, tracking issues to resolution<br />
&bull; Test all product deliverables for professional work, including the product, installation of product, and documentation for product<br />
&bull; Write and execute tests that verify internal API functions, user interface, and interoperability with between product modules<br />
&bull; Review requirements, design, code, test cases, and other documentation for potential issues<br />
&bull; Work with the development team, project management, and network operations to ensure that requirements are verifiable<br />
&bull; Plan, size, and schedule testing and certification activities<br />
&bull; Contribute to test strategies and master test plans<br />
&bull; Set up networked (IP) equipment for video content security tests in Windows, Linux, and Solaris<br />
&bull; Perform all system tests<br />
&bull; Execute certifications for embedded system implementations by partners (set-top boxes, connected TVs, etc.)<br />
&bull; Test and evaluate the system using the specified test procedure and initiate corrective action if required<br />
&bull; Document the test results in a test report<br />
&bull; Develop, configure and maintain test harness and/or test equipment used for tests and certifications<br />
&bull; Work with Set Top Box manufacturers to address issues<br />
&bull; Lead and mentor others in all the above<br />
&bull; Provide tier 3 technical support as needed<br />
&bull; Others as assigned</p>
<p>
This position reports to a technical manager within the engineering team.</p>
<p>
<strong>Required Qualifications:</strong></p>
<p>
&bull; 5-7 years software engineering work experience<br />
&bull; 4 or more years software testing experience<br />
&bull; 3 or more years client/server testing experience, particularly in Linux set top boxes<br />
&bull; Excellent understanding of typical software engineering practices (defect tracking, test case management, lifecycle models)<br />
&bull; Excellent analytical skills including root cause analysis in both software bugs and in processes<br />
&bull; Experience in QA activities for unit, component, system, smoke, regression, and automated testing including proven methodic approach to these is required (equivalence tests, boundary tests, state-transition, orthogonal arrays)<br />
&bull; Proven scripting/coding skills<br />
&bull; Excellent attention to detail and follow-through<br />
&bull; Excellent ability to work independently and in a team<br />
&bull; Strong analytical skills<br />
&bull; Tester-level proficiency in Linux and Windows<br />
&bull; Knowledge of<br />
o network principles and of TCP/UDP/IP technology<br />
o application, realization and use of the test system<br />
o RDBMS<br />
o Coding concepts such as OOP<br />
&bull; Basic proficiency in SQL<br />
&bull; Ability to identify weak points and risks<br />
&bull; Demonstrated attention to detail and high-levels of accuracy<br />
&bull; Excellent verbal and written communication skills including documentation in English<br />
&bull; Bachelors degree in computer science/electrical engineering or related field or equivalent experience</p>
