A <strong>Software Development Manager</strong> at Verimatrix participates in the creation of a large product suite that enables content protection and security for video delivered via satellite, cable, or the Internet.&nbsp; The development manager collaborates with his/her teammates to deliver high-performing, scalable, high-quality products.&nbsp; The manager should enjoy working through the software development lifecycle.&nbsp; A successful manager will be proactive, interactive, creative, and flexible.&nbsp;</p>
<p>
This position is responsible for managing the development of the software products assigned to the Development Manager.&nbsp; This includes reviewing and scheduling work requests, participating in scope definition for the products, driving the technical direction of the software products (in conjunction with the Software Architects and Product Managers), reviewing and approving requirements specifications, scheduling product versions, managing a team of software engineers, DBAs, and/or other technical specialists, leading project-level change control boards, overseeing the development of documentation to support the products, co-ordinating with QA leads and manager(s) to ensure the effective testing of the products, and other duties as assigned.&nbsp; Each team can have one or more leads as needed.&nbsp; The leads provide recommendations to the manager as well as assist in the daily management of the teams.</p>
<p>
The Software Development Manager will need to learn and understand the entire Verimatrix product suite as well as gain deep technical knowledge of particular solutions in the group he/she joins.&nbsp; We are a global company and appreciate people with global awareness and knowledge (languages other than English are a bonus).&nbsp;</p>
