<strong>GENERAL PURPOSE:&nbsp;</strong></p>
<p>
We&rsquo;re looking for QA Engineers, committed to quality and professional excellence, to measure the performance/scalability and redundancy of state-of-the-art Video Content Security products, in a fast-paced environment.</p>
<p>
<strong>JOB DUTIES &amp; RESPONSIBILITIES:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Measure performance (characterization and benchmarking) of our server/client video content security products.&nbsp;</li>
<li>
Collect, analyze, interpret, and communicate results on performance/scalability.</li>
<li>
Report diagnosed issues.&nbsp; Work with Engineering to better characterize the product.</li>
<li>
Set up and configure isolated IP networks/infrastructure (Linux/Windows) for testing and for reproducing reported issues. Identify issues with the test environment, or with the performance methodology, and resolve them.</li>
<li>
Accurately and concisely report both progress and defect status via Test Case and Defect Tracking databases.&nbsp; Track issues to resolution.</li>
<li>
Execute redundancy tests, as requested.</li>
<li>
Perform other duties and projects as assigned.</li>
</ul>
