<li>
2-3 years real-world software experience.</li>
<li>
At least 1 year experience in Linux / UNIX system administration.</li>
<li>
Excellent testing skills.&nbsp; Proven desire to obtain reliable, consistent, repeatable results.</li>
<li>
Knowledge of network principles (7 layer OSI model/subnetting) and of TCP/UDP/IP technology and troubleshooting required.&nbsp; Experience with network capture analysis tools - tcpdump, wireshark, fiddler, etc.</li>
<li>
Experience with Backend/Application Servers is essential.&nbsp;</li>
<li>
Previous experience administrating a relational database system - Oracle preferred but MS SQL Server, MySQL, etc. would be applicable.</li>
<li>
Good understanding of typical software engineering practices (Defect Tracking, Test Case Management, Lifecycle models.)&nbsp; Experience with Agile methods is a plus.</li>
<li>
Excellent analytical skills; attention to detail and follow-through.</li>
<li>
Excellent ability to work independently, as well as in a team environment.</li>
<li>
Strong written, verbal, and presentation skills.&nbsp; Excellent interpersonal skills.&nbsp; Self-motivated and energetic team player.</li>
</ul>
