A <strong>Senior Global Services Engineer</strong> at Verimatrix is that rare breed of being a blend of a highly-skilled engineer who also resolves the most complex and complicated technical issues while being customer-facing and helping other Global Services Engineers build expertise in Verimatrix&rsquo;s products and services.</p>
<p>
The Senior Global Services Engineers participate in the installation, configuration, acceptance testing, troubleshooting and maintenance of Verimatrix&rsquo;s content protection and security solutions for cable, satellite, IPTV and InternetTV operators worldwide. The Senior Global Services Engineer comes from a background in systems administration and/or network administration, and focuses on having a whole system view of how Verimatrix&rsquo;s products work within the larger ecosystem of off-the-shelf and custom solutions.&nbsp; A successful Senior Global Services Engineer will be proactive, interactive, creative, and flexible to anticipate questions and issues customers and partners may have, and provide that feedback into the Product Management, Engineering and Quality Assurance teams.&nbsp;</p>
<p>
We have several hundred customers in 96 countries, and appreciate people with global awareness and knowledge, so fluency in other languages is a bonus. Our team provides 24x7x365 support for customers and partners around the world. Our headquarters are located in San Diego, California with regional offices in Munich and Singapore.&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<strong>Some tasks the Senior Global Services Engineer will have include, but are not limited to:&nbsp;</strong></p>
<p>
&bull; Work with customers, partners, customer support, and other technical staff on the implementation design, configuration, optimization, migration, troubleshooting and ongoing maintenance for Verimatrix&rsquo;s products both on-site and remotely.<br />
